Description: Questar Fueling Co is a natural gas utility serving nearly a million homes and businesses in Utah.
Full Description: Questar Fueling is a newly formed subsidiary of Utah-based Questar Corporation. Affiliate companies include Questar Gas, a natural gas utility serving nearly a million homes and businesses in Utah, Wyoming and Idaho; Questar Pipeline an interstate pipeline company; and Wexpro a natural gas developer in the region. Prior to creating Questar Fueling, Questar Gas, the utility, first experimented with NGVs in 1981 when it converted 25 fleet vehicles and built a compressor station for fueling. For seven years, the company tested parts, made adjustments and improved the vehicle conversions and fueling process. By 1989, 21 of the original 25 vehicles were still on the road, a second station was installed, and Ford and General Motors began testing other vehicle models with the utility. The public also started showing interest, so the utility provided full public access to its two NGV-fueling stations. NGV MapBy the mid '90s, Questar's NGV fleet grew to more than 700 vehicles and the company moved NGV-fueling stations from its service centers to locations where the public and company could conveniently refuel. Ideally, this meant finding locations with branded gasoline stations where the owners would allow Questar Gas to lease space for the NGV-fueling equipment. Now Questar Gas operates 28 public NGV stations and has assisted the state in building five semi-public NGV stations, creating Utah's well-known Interstate-15 NGV-fueling corridor. In addition, the company has assisted many of its business-class customers with fleets install stations at their own facilities to fuel their NGVs. We have learned a few things about NGV fueling over the past 30 years and now we're offering our experience and services through Questar Fueling.

The Company was founded in 2000 to discover and commercialize targeted drug therapies for a broad range of ailments including cancer and diseases of the central nervous system (CNS). To fulfill this mission, TMC utilizes a patented in vivo drug discovery platform to identify, optimize, and validate the efficacy of lead molecules. This revolutionary approach yields novel molecules, precisely targeted to a disease tissue of interest, in a fraction of the time and cost of using traditional in vitro-based methods. TMC received its first invested capital through the establishment of a joint venture with Elan Corporation plc in October 2000. The focus of this collaboration is the development of targeted drugs for the treatment of cancer. In December 2001, we completed a first closing of a  $10 million Series B venture financing. Description: LoanKrunch is a next generation loan comparison engine dedicated to empowering consumers in the mortgage process by providing flexible
Headquarters Regions: Greater San Diego Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: LoanKrunch is a next generation loan comparison engine dedicated to empowering consumers in the mortgage process by providing flexible technology, information transparency and real loan comparisons.  LoanKrunch is true loan comparison engine, which places the consumer — not the loan officer, in control of the loan shopping process. The LoanKrunch patent pending expert rules engine compiles hundreds of rates and programs from multiple lenders daily, so the consumer can see all of the loan possibilities, including wholesale rates.  This completely transparent process can be done anonymously — no SSN, first name or last name needed. Searching takes seconds, and intuitive tools put the consumer in control, and gives them an easy way to filter, sort, and compare your options. Interested in a 30 year fixed term? A lower monthly payment?  Buy down the interest rate?  Once the consumer has found the appropriate loan — the LoanKrunch application process uses bank level data security to process your application through their lender partners — making it safe and secure.  And, when the consumer closes their loan, they'll get additional savings (on top of wholesale rates) with flat fee pricing—which can add up to a 50–90% savings vs. a traditional loan process. Securing a home loan is a serious and complicated financial decision, but LoanKrunch helps make it easier for consumers by providing an upfront way to see all available loan options and strategies anytime—all at an affordable price.
